{"ts":"2026-06-12T16:19:03.068Z","author":"maintainer-agent","op":"create","patch":[{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/id","value":"pm-r2kd"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/title","value":"pm templates: unknown subcommand + flags silently fall back to 'list' (exit 0) instead of erroring"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/description","value":"Repro (sandbox with @unbrained/pm-templates installed): 'pm templates apply bug --title \"Crash on logout\"' and 'pm templates frobnicate --whatever' both print the template list and exit 0. An agent that guesses 'templates apply' believes the template was applied when nothing happened — the opposite of the explicit-contract behavior pm plan has ('Unknown pm plan subcommand X. Allowed: create, show, add-step...'). Expected: unknown templates subcommand should error with the allowed list (list/save/show) and ideally hint that templates are applied via 'pm create <type> <title> --template <name>'. Likely cause: the templates command group treats unknown positionals as no-op and runs the default list action, also swallowing unknown flags like --title."},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/type","value":"Issue"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/status","value":"open"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/priority","value":2},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/tags","value":["agent-ux","dogfood-2026-06-12","packages","templates"]},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/created_at","value":"2026-06-12T16:19:03.068Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/updated_at","value":"2026-06-12T16:19:03.068Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/author","value":"maintainer-agent"}],"before_hash":"3cc22dff72be7b14824654a7a64ea62b04799939b2fee54c1b5f52ca60bf6df0","after_hash":"811b6df5d7de17136b10260a24bd2ea75bcf9b2398b774c3b5533527eff64918","message":""}
